animal.description:
We'd like you to meet... Stitch!

Stitch is a 3-year-old, male American Staffordshire Terrier who loves to play and cuddle. He is healthy, neutered, and current on all vaccines. He was adopted at a year old and has been living with a loving family for two years that had another dog. They were doing great together until recently, which is why we need to find Stitch another loving home.

He's a happy, loving dog and is crate trained. Stitch loves walks and playing fetch. Stitch is very puppy-like and he loves toys and you may even need to keep your socks off the floor as Stitch thinks those are toys.

He can get over-excited when playing with small children with high energy, so maybe kids a little older would be best. He may need to be the only dog in the family. If you'd like to meet Stitch, please submit a completed
adoption application found
at www.doggiebonez.com so that we can schedule a meet and greet. He is also on all of our social media pages IG: @Doggie_Bonez_Inc_ and Facebook: Doggie Bonez.

If adoption isn't an option, please consider fostering one of our pups. We are a volunteer-run non-profit dog rescue and always welcome new short and/or long term doggie foster families. We greatly appreciate the help and time of our fosters. You provide all the love, comfort, and safety of a home and we supply you with everything else you may need, dog food, dog bed, toys, medical attention (if needed), etc. If you are interested please visit www.doggiebonez.com to see all of our available dogs who need a foster family while waiting for their fur-ever home and complete the foster application.

Oh my gosh, this dog is ADORABLE! He is a petite-sized dog with a big personality! He absolutely LOVES tennis balls and is always determined to get two in his mouth at the same time, which he is able to do when he concentrates. He's very smart and eager to learn. He loves affection, treats, toys, walks, and baby pools. Link wants to be your only dog, as he can be pretty reactive to other dogs and would love all the attention. People also need to go slow with him and once he knows and trusts you, he's GREAT! He'd flourish in a quiet home without a lot of people/visitors coming and going since he can be people-selective. Because he's so playful and has a cute energetic personality, he'll need a yard with a block wall, so no apartments please. Link is about 1 1/2 years old, neutered, current on shots, microchipped, and his adoption would include an in-home training session. Still waiting on DNA tests to see what he is made up of--he's SO cute!

animal.description:
Tank is a handsome 5-year old male Boxer mix who was surrendered by his owner on June 24, 2020.

This good-looking guy has a tan short smooth coat with white markings on his chest, a long tail, and a sweet face with black shading around his eyes,  a dusting of white-and-black on his muzzle, and short semi-erect ears.

Tank has a sweet disposition and seems to love everyone when he is out of his kennel. He loves going for walks and playing with tug-of-war toys. Tank is not a huge fan of other dogs. 

Tank was a happy boy while he had his outdoor photos taken, and  he adored HSOV kennel tech Madison Barnett who helped him with his 'passport pictures'.  Tank is full of energy and seems much younger than the chronological age listed on his kennel card. This guy is truly ‘young at heart’ 

Tank weighs approximately 50 lbs and walks fairly well on a leash.   

Tank has already been neutered, so he could leave the shelter fairly quickly with an approved HSOV adoption application.

animal.description:
Curtesy post:

Allie, is Chance's side kick, a female, 4 yr old hound dog mixed breed. They are absolutely inseparable. Chance, a 7yr old male American bull dog with an adorable black patch over his eye. Chance is very, very smart.  He’s been through 5 weeks of boot camp and knows so many commands.  His trainer says he’s a thinker, a planner.  (In a good way, of course) Allie, well, she’s a goofy lizard master. She hunts for lizards all day and follows Chase around, copying everything he does.  The two absolutely love each other to pieces.  Chance and Allie can be a little picky with who they like so these two should be the only dogs in the family??. However, when on leash, Chance is trained to “leave it” and will walk right by all other dogs, walking with a loose leash, of course.  Allie just follows Chances lead.  Chance is such a lover and Allie so silly.  Both utd on vaccines, spayed, neutered, and microchipped.  These two were rescued from deplorable conditions from Long Beach, Ca. and have been waiting for their forever home for 7 months.  We don’t know why, they’re such special dogs. ??. If interested, Wendy @ 760-525-1480
Wendys5@twc.com

animal.description:
Hank is a loving 7 year old hound mix and weighs around 55lbs. He is a sweet boy who is looking for his forever home!

Hank has some anxiety living in a kennel environment and is looking for a calm and structured home where he can decompress and learn to trust and feel confident. Once settled, he enjoys being outside, going for walks, and using his nose. He requires a fenced yard where he can roam, sniff and lounge. He is not super high energy but will require 1-2 walks a day and time outside in a fenced area. 

Hank can be reactive with other dogs on leash, mainly due to his anxiety but has been fine with dogs that are calm and laid back out and about. Hank would like to be the only dog living in the home. Hank CANNOT be with cats. He could be older with kids over 8 that are respectful. 

Hank is UTD on shots, microchipped and neutered. His adoption fee is $400.

animal.description:
Sammy is a precious approx 9 mos old black mouth cur mix.  He is the cutest lil fella.  He is great with kids and other dogs. Happy-go-lucky description es this sweet boy!    He is playful, funny and is so cute to watch.  He is smart but clumsy as he is still very much a puppy and hasn’t grown into his legs yet. He loves to run and play with others.  He adores treats and head rubs!  He does great on a leash and is working on sit/stay command.  He needs his very own fur-ever family to grow up with.  Won’t you make him a part of yours?       

He is heart worm negative. 
All our adoption fees include spay/neuter, micro-chip, up-to-date vaccinations, including rabies thru date of adoption. This pup tested heartworm negative, and is on regular monthly heartworm prevention & on flea/tick prevention. 

In order to be considered for one of our beautiful pups, please go to our website and complete and application: https://www.mustluvdogs.org/adoptable-pets.
Please note that we are a DUE DILIGENCE adoption organization. Part of our approval process requires, among other things:
* Experienced pet home with verifiable vet references/history preferred, but we realize that everyone has to start somewhere, so all applications will be considered.
*The majority, but not all, of our pets require a fenced yard or secure enclosure.  In the case of apartments, we require Landlord approval and designated dog area in complex.
*Verifiable good veterinary history INCLUDING regular vaccination/visits and good Heartworm Prevention history is a MUST!
*Adopter must be able to have time to spend with the pup and be able to provide the pup a safe environment to live.
*ALL our dogs are expected to be primarily INSIDE dogs.  They MUST sleep inside the home.  We truly understand that some folks have working dogs (i.e. farmers, ranchers,etc); however, the majority of our dogs have had a rough life prior to coming to us & we want to make sure that they are showered with LUV & maybe even a bit spoiled for the rest of their lives. 

Other facts are also considered, including whether children or other pets are a good fit with the dog. 

Must Luv Dogs reserves the right to deny any applications that we don't think are a good fit with the pup. Our first & foremost concern is the dog's best interest. It is our MISSION to place them in a home that is a great fit for their needs for a lifetime of luv & being part of a family.
*We will consider adoptions in any area; however, will do not ship or transport puppies under the age of 12 mos. We will ONLY transport an adult dog on a transport approved by MLD, at adopter's expense.
* In order to be affordable and afford every family an opportunity to have a pup of their own, we keep our Adoption Fees low; however, please keep in mind that the fees we charge do not cover all costs for the pup.  Any additional donations are greatly appreciated!

Please note that all of our pets are in private foster homes. In order to reduce any stress or confusion for our pups, we require a completed, approved application BEFORE setting up a meet & greet for any of our pups.  Alternatively, you are always welcome to come meet any of our pups at one of our regular Adoption Events.   Our events are always posted on PetFinder OR on our Facebook page: https://www.facebook.com/mustLUVdogs.org.

Finally, THANK YOU for considering Must Luv Dogs for your next pet. 

*Most dogs require a fenced area in yard. 
*Apartments okay IF nearby dog park or walking trails (with landlord appoval).
*ALL dogs must be INSIDE dogs and treated a part of family. 
*We are a DUE DILIGENCE Adoption Rescue.  
*Must have good Vet history & Heartworm prevention is a MUST!
*ALL dogs are fully vetted, spay/neutered and microchipped prior to adoption.

FYI:   Even though this pup tested heartworm negative, we provide the following procedural information for your information:  Any of our pups who test HW+ are treated with the *slow kill method of treatment.   The *slow-kill method, simply stated, is a 30 day regiment of  doxycycline followed by a monthly dose of Advantage Multi for 12 months, then retesting.   Most dogs test negative after one year of following this treatment; however, we always recommend that potential adopters consult & follow the advice of their family veterinarian upon adopting any of our hw+ pups.   Although the fast-kill method is still considered the "gold-standard" by the AVA, and may be preferred by some vets; the slow-kill method has proven to be effective in our rescue. The main reason we utilize this method is due to our limited financial constraints and the high number of our rescue pups that are infected.   In the cases of severe infection and if the pup is highly symptomatic, we sometimes use the fast-kill approach instead.   Again, we recommend for you to consult with your veterinarian after the adoption is complete and follow their recommendations.

animal.description:
Mayella is listed as a Weimaraner mix. She is house broken and crate trained. For the first year of her life she had little to no contact with humans so she is extremely shy. Her only safety net appears to have been her siblings so she is completely dependent on being in a home with a dog friend. As far as people go, once see trusts you she is your shadow and loves massages. She loves going for walks and just being outside. Fast movements make her nervous so small children aren't an option. If you have a quiet household, are a patient person, a visible fence and another medium sized dog that loves to play she is your dog.

 You can also watch for stories, pictures and videos about me on our Facebook page https://www.facebook.com/groups/40103261297/ 

Adoption fee: $475.00 Adoption fees for all dogs/puppies include a $50 refundable training deposit. Complete your basic training program and provide a copy of the certificate within 4 months (120 days) of adoption and we will refund $50 of the original adoption fee. All dogs/puppies have been fully vetted including spay/neuter, micro-chipping, worming, heartworm testing and preventative treatment, flea/tick preventative, and all required age appropriate vaccinations. As required by Wisconsin Act 90, all dogs will have received a veterinarian exam (CVI) within the past 30 days. Our adoption process requires the submission of an application. Applications and Adoption Rules can be found on our website, on the "HOW TO ADOPT" tab at JRsPupsNStuff.org. Upon receipt of the completed application, we will process the application including: contact with your veterinarian and completion of a home visit. Please be sure to include the contact information for your vet as we will call. If your vet requires an information release, please be sure to contact them as soon as you submit your application. We are a group of volunteers with families and jobs, so please be patient and allow a few days for our response. JR's Pups-N-Stuff Dog Sellers License 270089-DS

animal.description:
Hi I'm Prairie! Do you like laying in the sunshine? Great, so do I! My foster dad lets me soak up the sun in our back yard and it's my favorite activity, besides playing with all my dog friends! I am the queen of zoomies and some say I hop around instead of run. I am very silly and love to show that by play bowing in front of you to get you to chase me or throw a toy for me. Cuddling in the recliner with my foster dad is the best, I like to be right next to him! I have been around cats and don't really pay them much attention, it's dogs I'm really interested in. In my forever home I'd love to have another dog to give me confidence and to keep me company when my human parents are busy. I'll show you how happy I am by smiling and wagging my tail, my smile is infectious! I can't wait to meet my forever family!

All of our pets start their journey in Memphis Tennessee where they remain in loving foster families until they are adopted.

In order to qualify for ALIVE Rescue Memphis's program all of the following steps must be met:

• You must be at least 21 years of age and be able to provide ALIVE with proof of age.

• Any current pets must be up to date on vaccinations, and be spayed/neutered. Exceptions to this will only be considered if proof of a medical explanation is provided.

• If you currently rent, you must provide a landlord’s phone number and a copy of your executed lease.

• All members of the family living in the home where the animal will be placed must be interviewed.

• Applicant must live within 50 miles of Memphis if interested in adopting and within 30 miles of Memphis if interested in fostering. 

•Allow an ALIVE Rescue Memphis representative into your home for a visit to insure that your home is safe for the potential new dog or cat.

•You must allow an ALIVE Rescue Memphis representative into your home for a visit to ensure that your home is safe for the potential new pet.

•You must be able and willing to spend the time and money necessary to provide training, medical treatment, and proper care for a pet.

•Currently, adoptions fees in Memphis are $275 for a dog over 4 months of age, $300 for a dog under 4 months of age.

•We require an additional $75 training deposit at the time of adoption. You will be required to enroll and complete a training class with your new companion at one of our approved training facilities. Once ALIVE Rescue Memphis receives proof of the completed class, this $75 deposit will be refunded.


Our adoption application can be found at http://www.aliverescuememphis.org/memphis-nashville-adoptions

Due to the extremely high volume of inquiries we receive, we ask that you submit an application immediately to start the adoption process. We try very hard to include all pertinent information in our bios. We are excited to help you find your new family member. However, ALIVE Rescue Memphis is operated 100% by volunteers. We want to spend our time saving dogs and assisting those adopters who have taken the time to complete an application. Thank you for understanding.

Breed selection is done in conjunction with two local vets and is not to be considered a guarantee but rather a well-educated decision from well qualified staff.

LIKE ALIVE Rescue Memphis on Facebook & Instagram!
Thanks for choosing rescue!!

animal.description:
Sasha is a young, beautiful Pyr girl looking for an active family to give her the attention and training she desires. She is house broken and does well with other dogs. Sasha would do great with an older dog sibling to learn from. She is still a pup and wants her new family to know that she will require training but will reward your patience with lots of snuggles! Sasha has spent the first few months of her life in busy environments and as a result displays some resource guarding behaviors and can take a little while to warm up to strangers, especially men. Like most of us these days, Sasha is not a fan of baths or manicures...but she is a fan of hot dogs, liver treats and belly rubs :) Sasha is looking for a fenced-in yard where she can get her puppy energy out and a patient family that has the time to dedicate to her training. Sasha is a very sweet and loving girl. With the proper training that she missed out on as a younger pup, she will be a great addition to the family!

NYS Registered Rescue # RR102
View full listing, fee and online application at - www.nationalpyr.org/adoptable-dogs (sorry, no phone submissions, but if you would like more information you can email us at renpyrgroup@yahoo.com).

Secure VISIBLE fencing is required; invisible fencing WILL NOT contain this breed. 

Our goal is to assess every application on its own merits. Key considerations are: 1) the experience of the applicant with large breed dogs 2) children in the household or regularly visiting the household are ready for a large-breed dog who is a guardian by nature (www.nationalpyr.org/know-the-breed) and 3) the sex of other dogs currently residing in the household to avoid same-sex aggression issues. For puppies under six months old, the applicant’s ability to socialize the puppy with older dogs is a priority.

animal.description:
Barry is not a lap dog (unless he decides he wants to be). Instead, he is a grumpy boy who came to us with a broken pelvis which still causes him pain. In the year he's been with us, Barry also suffered seizures and kidney stones. He's on a special diet and medication for all of these things, but he's still a grump. And we all still love him! 

Since being in our care, the poor guy has had to deal with puppies and big dogs who dont understand why he doesn't want to roughhouse. He does get along with dogs who aren't in his face and likes to fetch a ball as long as you don't try to take it back from him (Barry's rules).

Ornery as he is, Barry is kind of our mascot and we want the old guy to catch a break and live out the remainder of his life with someone he can find solace in. 

Barry loves to rub his back on the floor and wiggle and loves to have belly rubs by a person of his choosing. He enjoys certain members of our team while others simply arent his cup of tea.

To find out more about Barry, meet him and see if he's a match for you, text or call Julie at 435-773-5209.

animal.description:
Hi, my name is Sadie! I'm super sweet, easy going and love to snuggle. I'm an 8 year old rescue and a breast cancer survivor! Don't worry though, I'm cancer free now! I'm spayed and have had all my shots. These days I'm perfectly healthy! I get along great with kids and other dogs. My foster mom has a 11 year old and I'm great with him! (Unfortunately my foster mom doesn't have any friends with really little kids so we're not sure how I'll do with them).

My 2 favorite things in the world are snuggling and chew toys. I would do best in a home with an experienced dog owner because my foster mom says I still need quite a bit of training. I'm extremely smart, I just need a family with the time, knowledge and patience to help me get the hang of things. I'm really just hoping to find a loving family to call mine forever. I love snuggling, chewing on tennis balls and really just need a couple long walks a day and lots of love to be happy.

Sadie's Adoption fee is $200

Please email Kelly.V@HeidisLegacyDogRescue.com and fill out the application on our website HeidisLegacyDogRescue.com

LOCATED IN SAINT PETERSBURG, FLORIDA

$400 DONATION FEE
FULLY VETTED

In all seriousness, June was adopted out when she was three months old. We rescued an entire family of beagles including June's mother. They were living in horrible conditions, and all four of the adult beagles had heart worm disease. June was a wonderful puppy, and was very loving and happy.  Her family reached out to me for help when June started resource guarding. They loved her very much and she was part of their family. Unfortunately, they have 2 children under the age of five and there were a few incidents with June growling at the kids if they woke her up suddenly. They just couldn't take any chances, So here we are, June aka Sunny is back with Gimme Shelter, and we're looking for her perfect match. I would prefer a family that is experienced with Beagles and understands resource guarding behavior. She has been through obedience training and is a very smart dog. Sunny would do best with someone that will keep her busy with activities, and obviously no small children.

animal.description: While he may have the good looks of James Dean, this rebel has a cause - to be adopted! A two year old pitbull mix, Rebel was surrendered to our shelter when his owner was no longer able to care for him. A BIG boy, Rebel needs an owner who can not only handle his size but his energy. Though sweet and affectionate, he lacks basic manners and is more puppy than adult. While our staff has been working with him on leash manners and commands, he will need continued training once placed in a home. Due to his size and energy, Rebel should be placed with older children and in a home without cats. He is slowly starting to make canine friends at the shelter and would benefit from another dog his size to play with - he already has an admirer in Ella, who is notoriously picky about her friends! If interested in Rebel, email Vicki at Vicki@nokillarc.org

animal.description: Sugar Magnolia and Mr. Bojangles are a bonded pair of jack russell/ beagle mixes. Sugar Magnolia is a 2 to 3 year old female who weighs 18lbs. She arrived pregnant with her companion Mr. Bojangles, a 22 lb male, who is 1 to 2 years old. Unfortunately these 2 obviously suffered from  mistreatment and neglect in the past. They are a little fearful of new people .  They are housebroken but are trained to a dog door with a fenced yard.  These two must have a secure fenced yard that is attached to the house and one they cannot dig out of. An electric fence, kennel or run are absolutely not an option.  They have been around respectful children and have done fine; however, because they are fearful and are a flight risk if they get out of the fence, a quiet adult only home or one with respectful, older children is preferred. They are both good with dogs and cats but a prior situation with one of the cats they currently live with would  necessitate that they go to a home without cats or one where the cats can be kept separate when no one is home. They do get on furniture now, so if you don't allow dogs on furniture; these are not the dogs for you. These guys will require an experienced and patient home ( no first time dog owners). They cannot live in a city or suburban  environment  but rather require a quiet, rural area and a house (no apartments and you must own your home).  They are affectionate and playful dogs once they trust you. Mr. Bojangles is on a joint supplement due to a slightly abnormal gait in his right hind. If you are interested in adopting these two and meet all their requirements, go to www.journeyanimalrescue.org to submit an application. Only once an application is completely approved (including a vet check and home check) will a meet and greet be scheduled.  This requires all human and canine family members come to Fryeburg, Maine to meet them. Adoption fee for the pair is 700.

They cannot live in a city or suburban  environment  but rather require a quiet, rural area and a house (no apartments and you must own your home).  They are affectionate and playful dogs once they trust you but do have fear issues. Mr. Bojangles is on a joint supplement due to a slightly abnormal gait in his right hind. If you are interested in adopting these two and meet all their requirements, go to www.journeyanimalrescue.org to submit an application. Only once an application is completely approved (including a vet check and home check) will a meet and greet be scheduled.  This requires all human and canine family members come to Fryeburg, Maine to meet them. Adoption fee for the pair is 700.

Our sweet senior girl Zelda came to us on death's door.  She was a skeleton with a layer of skin on top.   Starved almost to death, we were not sure if she would make it, but our girl is a fighter.  Since she was found abandoned, emaciated, and very sick, she has had two growths removed, heart worm treatment and is diabetic.   More than likely due to her diabetes, she has lost her vision.    
She has been through it, but is still a happy girl, who loves to snuggle but still likes to go walking and play a bit.    She needs a special person who does not mind giving her insulin twice a day ( vetsulin), taking her on a walk or two and letting her snuggle with you when she naps.
If Zelda is a perfect addition to your family, please  let us know.


The on line application for her adoption is below. Please note, we do the following
1. on line application
2. vet and reference check
3. phone call
4. home visit
5 meet and greet
6. adoption
We will travel up to two hours to do home checks. We also truly feel the dogs in our rescue have been through enough. We take in those who are injured, abused, neglected, sick, and abandoned. That being said we search for a home that they are never put in that position again. No more hurt or fear.

animal.description:
Daffadil is in foster 
 She wins the hearts of everyone she meets. Daffo is a 5 year old Pit Bull mix that loves to be the center of attention. This Angel is very easy to fall in love with. She didn't do well in the shelter environment, but is thriving in her foster home. She has not had any potty accidents, only barked a few times, and likes having a daily routine. Her foster Dad says she is a very easy dog to take care of. Daffo has to be on a strict hypoallergenic diet and is also on Apoquel daily for allergies. She loves to run in her fenced yard and play with KONG squeaky balls she looks like a bucking pony when she chases the balls and going on car rides. When in the home she likes to snuggle and is fine left out on her own when her foster Dad is at work. She also likes to wear sweaters, sweatshirts, or T-shirts. You need to be over 21, a homeowner, and commit to keeping her on her hypoallergenic diet and meds. Apply at:
Tapsshelter.org

Daffadil is an insecure dog that needs a quiet, only pet environment. When things are quiet and calm, she can peacefully co-exist with another dog, but she is easily startled by loud noises such as fireworks, and becomes over-stimulated by both noises and active dog play and becomes dog aggressive. Daffadil also has many allergies and requires a prescription allergen-free diet, which isn't much more costly than a normal quality food diet. Your vet can give you a prescription and you can order directly from Chewy or another mail order company right to your door. She also requires a monthly medical prescription that can be between $75-$100/month. We are also suggesting a home without children under the age of 12 due to loud noises/fast movements making her uncomfortable. 

She is a special girl that is looking for a quiet home where she can be the queen.

animal.description:
Meet Charlie!

This poor guy was recently surrendered to us from his owner. They are moving into a small apartment with 4 kids and could not take him with them. The kids were heartbroken and even wrote Charlie a goodbye letter that tugs our heartstrings.

Charlie was nervous when his owners left him for the first time at our vet. We soon learned that he is deaf and could not hear our assurances. His owners never mentioned this to us. Charlie received his updated vaccines and he was able to get neutered and microchipped. 

Charlie went into a temporary foster home, and he did well adjusting to an entirely different lifestyle. Since he is deaf, we put Charlie through professional training to work on physical and visual commands and affirmations that are usually given verbally. He has been doing really well with his training! The trainers will teach adopters how to work with him, and teach adopters what Charlie has learned. We are looking for a home that can help guide him along in life since he is already at a disadvantage. He does need a proper introduction with new people, and we would not recommend a home with a lot of foot traffic (meaning you would need Charlie to meet a bunch of new people). He is a total sweetheart with people he is comfortable with and he is just looking for a new constant. Charlie loves to play with toys, and he would like to go for walks (he does GREAT on a leash with his new training) or play in the yard. He LOVES cuddle time. That is a must.

Charlie is about 2 years old and weighs 80 lbs. He is neutered, micorchipped, up to date on vaccinations, and heartworm negative.

Email us at info@adorehouston.org with questions about Charlie. If you would like to apply to adopt him, the link is www.adorehouston.org/adoption-application/

animal.description:
Savannah is one of our long-time LoveyLoaves residents, and she is in need of a forever home to call her own. Savannah came to us in September 2019 with a bullet lodged in her spine and a fiery, rowdy, and feisty spirit. Over the last year, she has undergone surgery and a long recovery to remove the bullet, she’s done countless hours of acupuncture, aqua treadmill, and laser therapies, and she was neglected and uncared for by a previous foster causing major setbacks… Although the bullet did permanent damage and she will not walk unaided on her own, all of the various therapies she has been through over the last year have increased her mobility, increased her energy, made her stronger overall.

Savannah's ideal home is one with no men, no children, and no other pets. Savannah will thrive best in a home as an only dog in an active household. She is a young dog and she loves to play and be outside and run. She is paralyzed in her back end due to being shot in the spine, and she uses a cart for play and exercise time. She does require bladder expression (manually squeezing urine from the bladder) which is quick, clean, and easy to do.

We need a hero to open their heart and home to this special girl

***
LoveyLoaves is a specially-abled dog rescue based in Orlando, FL. We work to rehabilitate and rehome dogs who have special needs and have been dealt different circumstances in life. The LoveyLoaves adoption application is available at www.LoveyLoaves.org. Prior to being turned over to their forever families, LoveyLoaves requires an adoption fee per dog to cover vetting including neuter, microchip, and vaccinations. Medical records will be transferred to the new pet guardian upon adoption. If you have questions about this dog or about the LoveyLoaves adoption process please feel free to contact us at (407) 446-2245 or at cheri@loveyloaves.org.

animal.description:
Friends to the Forlorn
Adopt-a-BullBreed: Pit Bull Terrier Gender: Male Estimated Date of Birth: April 23, 2015 Size: 45 lbs Location: Dallas, GA
RESCUING VICTOR
Victor was a cruelty case out of Newton County. He was found in a pen, tethered and couldn't reach food or water. Victor was stuck outside, starving to death. He was so thin, a woman's bracelet could've fit around him. At 5 years old, this poor guy had a body score of 0.75, weighing in at a scant 21 pounds when he should've been at least 50 pounds. Of course, Victor was also heartworm positive. While most rescues were shutting down intakes due to COVID-19, we kept going and Victor got his freedom ride on April 21, 2020.
ABOUT VICTOR
Victor has put on weight and is a happy, healthy boy. He is a quiet, sweet boy who is housebroken and crate-trained. He underwent heartworm treatment in August 2020 and he will be neutered a few weeks later and ready to go into an adoptive home. We estimate this to be sometime in September 2020.
Our adoption fee is $300. All dogs are current on vaccinations, spayed or neutered, micro-chipped, on heartworm prevention, and are fed top of the line grain-free food.www.savingpitbulls.org

animal.description:
Introducing Rain! 

This little girl is Catahoula, possibly a mix.

She has been in a loving foster home since the age of seven weeks old.
Rain is completely deaf, and close to blind. She does see shadows.

Rain is 13 weeks old now, and is ready for her forever home.
As you can see, she loves to play, and would do best in a home with another dog that would like to play with her. Children who would like to play with her would be fine as well :-)

She loves a kiddy pool, running in the yard, and her toys.  She thinks car rides are the best!

She has a very comfortable bed  in her foster home and comes with her harness, matching leash and some toys.

Rain is spayed, and up-to-date on vaccinations. 
Someone who has experience with deaf/blind dogs would be great. Keep in mind that you cannot call her, she doesn’t listen to commands, because she can’t hear you :-)

Let us know if you’d like to meet this baby!

This pup can be adopted by going to our web site www.homesforpets.org and filling out one of our applications.

animal.description: Hi! My name is Benjamin! I am a 2-year old silver purebred silver Weim looking for a home to call my own. I am a little on the smaller side for a Weim, but what I lack in size, I make up for in personality. I can be a little pushy and bossy with other dogs so I need a dog in my home that will keep me in line a bit but not be overly alpha or aggressive. I am a lover not a fighter but my Foster Mom says that I can be like an annoying little "gnat" around other dogs as I do not always understand doggie spatial boundaries. I do like to play though and would enjoy another canine companion to hang out with. Mom says I need a canine sibling that can teach me some better dog-dog manners!I am submissive to my people and really want to please and am more comfortable following a confident "hoo-man" who is the leader of the pack! I was surrendered to GLWR because I was too worried about protecting my people and they did not have the environment or the skills to help me learn how to respond when meeting new folks. I just didn't understand my role in my home. My foster Mom says I have really come a long way and with the right home, patience, training, love, and snuggles I can finally let my guard down and be my true Weimaraner self! If you want a fun loving, snuggle bug little fella that wants to be your best bud than I am the guy for you. Mom says that I am extra special so my family needs to be extra special too!

animal.description:
You can fill out an adoption application online on our official website.Online Adoption Application
Hospice Foster, Not for adoption

It takes a special person to take in a Hospice Foster. Sawyer was neglected for years before arriving in a shelter. He also had a sister that we tried to save but sadly she was very sick and the Vets said the humane thing to do was to end her suffering. It was one of the hardest decisions. it's a horrible thing to try to save a dog and in the end fail them. Sawyer's heart is very enlarged, he is at the end stages of heart failure due to heart-worm for way too long. He is on a few heart medication until he passes and on a slow kill heart-worm treatment, but sadly we don't know how much longer his heart will last. He does have some bad days, but his good days are awesome days because of Sarah. He is spoiled and loved until the time comes. These dogs do not deserve the hands that they were dealt, but we can all help them by being strong and taking them into our heart and homes. So, we want to thank Sarah Simpson for giving him his best life, and Anyone who contributed to him. It's a very selfless act and needs to be commended, as not many of us can do it, but each dog deserves it.

animal.description:
Tuco is a sweet dog who loves attention. He enjoys playing with people, but he also likes to just hang out with them. Water and jolly balls are his two favorite toys. He loves these things so much that it can be difficult to pull him away from them.
Born in 2015, Tuco came to Best Friends from a shelter in California. He will guard food and has shown other guarding behaviors. Tuco also has some handling issues, especially during medical checkups. He especially doesn't like having his feet or ears touched. His caregivers at the Sanctuary are working with him to decrease his food guarding and to improve his ability to be handled. 
Tuco has done well with all the dogs he's met at the Sanctuary and has even passed a cat test here. He has also lived with small dogs successfully before. When the weather is warm, Tuco could happily live in the Dogtown dog park pool, but he'd be even happier to go home with you.

animal.description:
**A BIG THANK YOU TO ZIGGY SCHUMACHER (AN ALL 4 PAWS ALUM!) FOR PARTIALLY SPONSORING SALEM'S ADOPTION FEE**

This gorgeous girl is so deserving of a wonderful home that will give her all the love, attention, and care she was deprived of for so long. Salem is a 6.5 year old spayed female lab/terrier mix who weighs 55 lbs. Salem and her friend, Abraham, were seized from their neglectful owners last year. They were forced to call a chaotic shelter home for seven months as a court case was brought against their former "family." We were happy to save Salem and bring her to a wonderful foster home. Being a loved family pet was totally new to Salem when we first rescued her, but she has learned to love napping on couches, playing with toys, and snuggling with her foster family. She gives the sweetest kisses too! Salem is a bit shy in new situations, but who can blame her after having such a rough start to life? Because she can be shy at first, she is looking for a home without young children who may overwhelm her. New sights and sounds are still a little scary, so she'd benefit from a calm home in a quieter neighborhood. She loves spending time outside, exploring everything the great outdoors has to offer. This silly girl can't help but want to chase small critters, so she will need a home without small pets, including cats. She has been very selective with her doggie friends, so we feel she needs to be the center of her new forever familes home as an only pet. Salem seems to be housebroken, is comfortable in her crate, and and is food motivated. Please help us find Salem the forever family she has waited her entire for!

Interested in adopting? Take the first step and complete an adoption application on our website: https://www.all4pawsrescue.com/
We are a foster based organization so we do not have a facility to visit. Please visit our FAQs to learn more: https://www.all4pawsrescue.com/faq
Find us on Facebook for foster updates and a full list of our adoptable pets: https://www.facebook.com/all4pawsrescue/

animal.description:
Kollin is a sweet and happy boy looking for his forever home! He was found abandoned with his siblings when he was around 3 months old. Kollin found a home and was healthy and happy for a while. As he got older, he started to develop anxiety that turned into aggression when around other dogs. Unfortunately, he is no longer a good fit in the home he is in now since there are other dogs he doesn't get along with. His anxiety is starting to take a toll on his health, and we believe he will be much happier in an only-animal home!  

He is a super fun, spunky doofus that would love a nice quiet place with a big yard for him to zoom in and throw his toys around. He is fixed, up to date on all vaccines, and crate trained. He would do best in a home without other animals and without small children. He loves to cuddle and ride in the car and will make a wonderful companion for the right person! Belly rubs and long hikes are the way to this boy's heart and when he loves a person, he loves them with everything!

Email beaglebasecamp@gmail.com for any questions or inquiries!

animal.description:
SOFIA IS SPECIAL NEEDS AND IS IN NEED OF A SPONSOR, SHE IS NOT AVAILABLE FOR ADOPTION

Hello everyone,

My name is Sofia and my personality is as big as my beautiful name. I'm a 5-year-old small 8-pound Bichon Frise mix. I am fun, loving and full of spirit! They call me a SPECIAL NEEDS PUP. I took a fall before becoming a BROC BABE and the doctors said I would NEVER walk again due to a spinal cord rupture. But my foster mom says I have the will to get wherever I want, nothing holds me back. My BROC Aunties got some custom wheels for me and you should see me run. I'm like a horse in its chariot, and I must say, I do look adorable. I take walks with and without my wheels, I walk with all my fur siblings and chase bunnies like no other but I need my wheels at times.

My foster mom loves me and takes great care of me. I am still practicing walking and recovering and could use some help with my medical bills and daily needs. If you'd like to sponsor me, please use the link below. Thank you!

Sponsor Me: https://bichonrescueoc.org/sponsorship

animal.description:
We would like for you all to meet MJ, or as we lovingly call her: Big Mama!
Nearly four years ago, Big Mama's family reached out to us for help with her litter of puppies although they wanted to keep mom. We took in her 7 puppies and they became the "A Pups!" Those 7 babies found woderful homes and the familyreached out to us now, all these years later, to surrender her.
This golden girl is a mere 8 years old and you wouldn't know it at all! She is full of life and is as strong as an ox. She rolled into rescue at 78 lbs, but she lost 8 lbs and looking so much better! 
Big Mama likes other dogs, but she can be reactive towards negative behaviors from other dogs. She is curious of all dogs and loves to see our own pups (she loves our Scout and Maizy!), so she can have doggie friends, they just need to be pretty low key. Definitely no cats! 
MJ has met plenty of kids in the neighborhood and she appreciates their attention as much as any other person--she simply ADORES people of all shapes and sizes! She has not met a stranger. 
MJ is the perfect companion. She loves attention but she does not seek it out--zero demands! She will sit by your side for hours on end, she is just happy all day long. 
MJ is working on leash skills. This is her only challenge. She can be pretty stubborn which makes a leash walk pretty time consuming, but we are working on it!
Her day here consists of:
1. Early morning rise, out to the lawn with foster dad to lounge while he reads the news. Mid-morning siesta on the deck in the sunshine
3. Late morning snuggles with (insert any family member here)
4. Early afternoon siesta on the deck in the shade
5. Chase squirrels until dusk
6. Snuggle, siesta, snuggle...
If you have never considered adopting a senior--they are full of wonder and life and are so freaking low-maintenance! As easy as they come!
MJ is being fostered in Decatur, GA. $150 to adopt this beauty! For more info: www.pmarinc.org
animal.name: MJ (aka Big Mama)

animal.description:
Oz is a handsome 3-year old male Labrador Retriever/Pit Bull Terrier/Boxer mix who was surrendered by his owner on June 19, 2020 along with a few of his best friends who shared his previous home including Pirate and Wizard (Labrador Retriever/Pit Bull Terrier/Boxer mixes) and Shaggy (Beagle).

Oz has a white short smooth coat, a long tail, and a noble-looking face with dark brown eyes, a black/pink nose, and large white floppy ears which are sprinkled with black spots.

Oz is understandably 'out of his element' being in an unfamiliar place with folks that he doesn't yet know or trust :)   Oz is a very frightened boy and wasn't ready to venture from the security of his kennel for outdoor photos ...  so we opted to take preliminary pictures on June 20th on his kuranda bed with a promise to take more flattering ones at a later date.

Oz weighs 55 lbs. He will be neutered before being adopted by his new family.

Oz was neutered on July 29, 2020 and was also given rabies vaccine.

This girl is the dog to have if you are a single pet owner! You could not ask for a better companion! Brown Sugar thrives on people's attention and love. She loves to go for rides, walks, plays ball ... one of the all around greatest dogs ever! We are shocked she is still here! Brown Sugar needs to be an only dog. She loves people more than anything but absolutely has to be the only dog. Even if you have dog visitors, or want to frequent dog parks... she is not the girl for you. Although this may seem like a big set back, its really not if you have no other dogs and enjoy hiking or driving around and need a great companion. She is a strong girl. animal.description:
Meet Bindi,
Bindi is a very special 4 year old female Pitbull mix looking for a special home she can call furever. 

Bindi’s home must have:
A fenced yard (4 feet or taller)
1 or more dogs her size or larger (about 55lbs)
No Cats
No Children – even as visitors
A strong reliable confident handler
Not much is known about Bindi’s life before she came to WOFAR, what we do know is that it must have been a rough one.
In her time with us Bindi has learned to play with other dogs and to rely on them for companionship and social cues in a variety of situations; she has also learned techniques that help her rely on her handler and their tools to maintain a safe working relationship and environment.
Bindi is a dog with a lot of anxious energy but she has learned to thrive in an environment that uses structure and routine to help her expend that energy through training, exercise, and play. Some of Bindi’s favorite energy burning activities include:
Agility style weave poles
Structured and redirected walks
Controlled hiking
Yard play
Hide and seek
Basic obedience drills
In her current foster home Bindi has shown that she readily accepts her roll as a member of a four-dog pack. She also recognizes that her foster mom holds total authority. HOWEVER, she will push back from time to time and does challenge the authority of other humans in the house; she is a real boundary pusher and it is important that her furever family recognize that and be prepared to set and enforce strong firm boundaries. 
To get Bindi to where she is in her training we have utilized tools that sometimes carry a stigma and her continued success will depend on her families willingness to use those tools which include:
A Prong Collar
A Muzzle
A Drag Leash
A Short Lead
A Solid/Indestructible Crate
Some of Bindi’s other favorite activities include:
Snuggling
Eating
Leisure Walks
Car Rides
Bindi is the kind of snuggle buddy that does all she can to share your skin and while her foster family loves this, it is a behavior they recognize should be limited and monitored as it can lead her to expressing possessive behaviors in an unhealthy manner. 

Bindi is house trained to a schedule, and crates easily.
When home alone Bindi can be left to roam the house with calm non-destructive dogs without a problem. However, she will join the party if someone else starts it.
Currently, Bindi sleeps in her own bed beside her handler at night; she does push for being in the bed with her handler but this should not be permitted.
Bindi knows and understands the basics of obedience but they represent a struggle within her and as such practicing them daily is an amazing way to expend mental and physical energy.
Bindi is anxious and shy about meeting anyone canine or human while on leash or when they care coming into her space; her foster mom has worked with her to develop a routine and procedure for meeting new friends in both circumstances so that everyone is safe and successful.
In addition to her training and behavioral needs Bindi has bad eyes. She has learned to accept her twice daily drops with little to no push back; and also takes Benadryl to help control it all.
Bindi’s Foster mom is dedicated to working with her furever family and home to set everyone up for success by showing them how to use the training tools and techniques that have gotten Bindi to where she is today and helping to set routines and schedules.

animal.description:
Hi, I'm Bernard, formerly known as Willie, and I'm a total sweetheart. I'm about 6  1/2 years  and am about 30lbs.  I'm tri-color and am very cute.  Everyone who meets me comments on how adorable and sweet I am.

It is particularly amazing that I'm so sweet given how I spent the first part of my life.  Believe it or not, I lived at the end of a chain.  I was a "hunting dog" but mostly just laid around a grassless yard with no place to go.  There were a bunch of other beagles in the yard but we didn't really get to play since we were all on chains and couldn't reach each other.  

Miraculously, this amazing group of people came in and talked the hunter into giving me up.  Now I live with another dog and a human kid and life is sooooo much better.  I can walk around all day long if I want in our fenced in yard and I sleep on comfy beds.  I love to nap on the patio.   Life is so great now and I have become accustomed to it quite nicely.  

I am up to date on my vaccines and am microchipped and am on monthly preventatives.  I'm scheduled to be neutered in March.  (That was the first available appointment we could get!!)

I have something called "cherry eye".  Basically a gland in my eye is bulging out.  It sounds and looks worse than it is.  It is fairly common.  Also the vet looked at it and said that it is not causing any problems and he does not recommend any treatment for it at this time.  But while I'm under anesthesia for my neuter, we'll see if the vet can do anything about it. 

I'm a pretty chill guy.  At 6+ years old, I like to get in some exercise during the day but I also am a champion napper and sleeper.  I walk nicely on a leash and I'm crate trained.  

Also, my foster mom said that I had to mention that I have dimples.  It doesn't get cuter than that!  

And I'm a really good snuggler!!!

I'm looking for a forever home where I can make up for lost time.  I can't wait to be a pet and get lots of love and attention.  If you would like to meet me, please contact karenquinn14@gmail.com.

Thanks so much.

Bernard

animal.description:
Blitzen is a 5-year-old, 65 lb. Great Pyrenees/German Shepherd mix looking to find her forever home. She is a sweet-natured dog with her people.  Typical of her breed, she is loyal, loving, and sweet to those she trusts.  She is house trained and a dream on a leash.  She is certainly a beautiful girl!

She needs to be the only pet in her castle, so no other dogs or cats can share her space.  Only kids over 12 for Blitzen and she will need a fenced yard.  Blitzen is not a candidate for apartment or condo living or first-time-dog-owner and she will need someone with breed experience. 

If you are interested in learning more about Blitzen, please complete an application then reach out to Debbie@bigfluffydogs.com. Please apply online, at https://bigfluffydogs.com/adopt/adoption-application/. 

Our main website, www.bigfluffydogs.com has more information about us and the rescue process. 

NOTE TO EMAILERS FROM PETFINDER: WE DO NOT RESPOND TO EMAIL INQUIRIES WITHOUT AN APPLICATION. WE REGRET WE CANNOT RESPOND TO EVERY EMAIL, BUT UNLESS YOU FILL OUT AN APPLICATION, WE DO NOT KNOW YOU EXIST. 

All known information about an individual dog is provided in its listing. We do our best to provide accurate information, but adopters should understand that each home is different and the dog may behave differently in a new home. Dogs are creatures of their environment and you help make the dog what it will be. Homes considering adopting a puppy must be prepared for 1.) Flexible schedules for potty training. Puppies can only hold it for one hour per month of age (i.e. a 4-month-old puppy can only go 4 hours without a potty break). 2.) Crate training until the puppy is at least one year old to prevent chewing on inappropriate things when you can't supervise. 3.) Socialization.  The more positive and varying experiences as a puppy the better, both in and out of your home. 4.) Puppy behavior and life stages are equivalent to a human toddler. It takes at least a full year to have a calmer, well-adjusted dog. Patience is required and when your dog's behavior is a positive experience for you and those around you, your patience will be rewarded ten-fold, for years to come.  Please do not consider adopting a puppy if you have not thoroughly thought through the pros and cons of having one. So many people end up returning them after 3-5 months because they didn't realize the amount of work involved in raising a puppy.  Patience, appropriate toys, socialization, and obedience training are all musts. All are time-consuming and can be expensive. All dogs require supervision with children and obedience training. Adopters that want to have good dogs must be prepared to put the time and effort into training a dog. Any dog requires work and effort, but a well trained, well-socialized dog is more than worth the effort to get them there.

animal.description:
Riddle is a 4-year-old male (55 lbs.) who was rescued from Memphis Animal Services.  

He is quiet in his crate and very clean.  He is a well mannered dog who has a very sweet nature.  He has not pottied in his crate or in the house.  He is working on his obedience commands and so far he has mastered “Come” and “Sit.”  

Riddle loves hiking in the woods behind his foster home; hiking brings out the puppy in him.   

Riddle is currently living in a foster home in the Memphis area, where for the first time, he is learning the ropes of being a pampered pooch.

Riddle has heartworms, and he has begun the slow kill treatment for his heartworms.  

Because Riddle has some scarring from his past life, we think it is best that he be an only dog.  He will need a securely fenced yard and to be monitored when he is outside exercising.  Why?  Because he can climb as well as a cat!!!  

He is looking for an ultra loving and responsible home that will give him security, love and a solid routine.  Riddle is on the search for his perfect family.

If you would like to be considered for adoption, please complete the adoption questionnaire on our website www.heartsofgoldpitrescue.com.

*4 years old
*Housetrained
*Crate trained
*Wants to be the only dog

animal.description:
ATTENTION: PLEASE READ THROUGH TO SEE WHETHER YOU MEET OUR ADOPTION CRITERIA BEFORE RESPONDING. IF YOU MEET OUR CRITERIA FOR ADOPTION OF THIS DOG, PLEASE FOLLOW THE LINK TOWARD THE BOTTOM OF THE PROFILE TO COMPLETE OUR APPLICATION. THANK YOU!

Meet Froy!

Froy is a lovely, sweet, 3 year old GSD who came to Indigo Rescue in very sad shape. Her owner passed away and she had terrible skin allergies which had caused her to lose all of her hair. Her skin was purple and inflamed. She was not well socialized with other dogs.

Enter the beauty of a loving foster home! We put Froy on a prescription diet for allergies, and her foster used a medicated shampoo and rubbed coconut oil into her inflamed skin. Froy responded wonderfully! Within less than a month her skin was recovering, and now, just a few months later her coat has grown in beautifully. Froy did turn out to have a hypothyroid contributing to her skin issues so she will need to continue taking medication for that.

Froy is a sweet girl who true to her breed, is her human’s shadow. She has learned how to play and interact with other dogs in her foster home and now she can tolerate her person being out of her sight as long as she is with another dog companion. She’s a bit of a toy hog, and she’s a bit mischievous, but she gets along very well with dogs who are friendly and playful. Froy can still be barky when she sees other dogs while on a walk. She responds well to good leadership though. 

Our criteria for placement of Froy are; a commitment to her allergy diet and medication, a securely fenced yard, a human or humans with dog leadership skills, and a friendly dog companion who is not a senior dog.

Adoption Process: We are not first come first served. Indigo Rescue focuses on finding good matches between dogs and families to ensure life long adoptions. We deliver all dogs to their new homes. All of our dogs are in foster homes. 

If you’re interested in meeting one of our dogs, please use the following link and complete our Adoption Application. You can either scan your completed application and email it to us at: info@indigorescue.org, or you can fax it to us at: 888-502-7660.
The link is not live, so you will need to copy and paste it into your browser: https://storage.googleapis.com/gator-users/user-680788/documents/d1742bff02e44c2ea25649cb45df5103/Pet%20Application%20Form%20December%202020.pdf
If the dog you're interested in seems compatible with your lifestyle we'll set up a time for you to meet the dog privately.
PLEASE NOTE: Indigo Rescue only adopts to homes within 30 miles of Beaverton because our volunteers deliver all of our dogs to their adoptive homes. We work very hard to create a family of our Indigo Rescue adopters because we want to be close enough to help in case there are any problems. We want everyone to be happy and successful!

**ALL of our dogs, puppies, cats, kittens and rabbits come vaccined to their age, spayed/neutered and microchipped.

Thank you for your interest in adopting and saving a life.

animal.description:
Dah lings -- Hello! Dee Dee here with my views on the proper habitat for someone such as myself you know, a beautiful, highly intelligent, young girl that is often mistaken as a potbelly pig (which is soooo offensive!). As it appears, my spunky personality, beautiful looks, perfect pizza ears, are not enough these days as I am still sitting in the shelter imploring these people to get me a home. They obviously are not doing a good enough job, so here I am typing this myself! All a girl like me needs is the following:
1. Luxurious accommodations (a fluffy bed, a warm lap, and some toys for me to play with) 
2. Decadent meals (lovely kibble served in a bowl diamond chipped preferably - with a tall glass (or bowl) of water)
3. Exquisite landscaping (beautiful green grass for me to roll around on)
4. Benevolent family (people who will find me as amazing as I find them, who will rub my belly, play with me, take me for runs, and allow me to kiss them incessantly if I so chose)
Despite my many wonderful qualities, since I am 45 pounds of playfulness, and I like to chase small furry things, you might not want to have a cat, or other dogs. I am all you need. So, tell me, are you able to provide me the proper habitat I require? Or do you know someone who is? Please share with them my post! Thanks Dah-lings! Tah Tah!

If you're interested in adopting (or fostering!) one of our Don't Bully Us Rescue puppies or dogs please go www.dontbullyusrescue.org and fill out an online application. You can also go to our website www.dontbullyus.com for adoption, volunteer and foster applications. If you know the name of the pup, add it to your application. If you don't know the name of the puppy, just add a brief description of it! After approving your application, we will contact you for a meet and greet!

We have dogs ranging from newborn puppies to senior dogs in our rescue all looking for their forever homes. You can check out our latest pictures of our adoptable pups and dogs on our Facebook page at www.facebook.com/dontbullyusrescue . Also on our Facebook Page check out our Event section, this will tell you were we will be for our next adoption event. We usually have adoption events every weekend, giving you the chance to meet some of our wonderful adoptable pups in person. Thank you for taking the time to check us out, we look forward to receiving your application!

Please note: Due to restrictions and bans on bully breeds, we are unable to adopt out to renters and active Military personnel but we are working on changing perspectives and discriminatory Breed Specific Legislation for these wonderful dogs!

animal.description:
Handsome Strong Boy Bronson is looking for his forever homeBronson is a very handsome one year old red male that was surrendered to DRM because his owners were not experienced enough to handle him after they adopted him from a shelter. He is crate trained, and once his foster mom tells him it's time to go to the crate, he will open the crate door by himself and go in and wait for his good boy treat. He is house trained and fairly good on a leash. Bronson will require a home with breed expertise and structure. He would do best in a home with no cats or kids as he is a pretty rambunctious boy with a strong prey drive. He is learning everyday in his foster home.

Bronson loves to play with toys. If it's a toy he can chase, make squeak, or shake the life out of, it's a favorite toy. Bronson will play independently, but his favorite games are fetch and tug of war, and for those games he pretty much insists you play with him. He also loves to go for rides in the truck and is learning good manners on the road. One of his favorite down time activities is to lay in front of the deck windows soaking up the sun and watching the world go by. He especially likes to lay his head in your lap to get a head and neck massage. Bronson is very smart and very food motivated, which is a great combination for learning commands and behaviors quickly. He has learned sit, down, wait, stay, shake (either paw based upon which hand you put out), leave it, etc. He has also learned to sit and wait to eat until he is released to eat, and many other good manner behaviors.

Bronson is an awesome dog, and will be required to go to a home with a big fenced in yard to run and play in, and with people who understand what it takes to be a pack leader.

This fabulous foster is a Doberman Rescue Minnesota foster dog.

Please read all adoption steps and policies carefully on our website. http://dobermanrescueminnesota.com/adoption-steps/

Qualified adopters are within the approved adoption area, and Adopter will be requested to visit this foster dog at the foster family home. Our foster families are generally located within a 250 mile radius of Minneapolis, MN.

All DRM dogs are spayed/neutered, vaccinated, health checked, microchipped, 4DX tested, and on monthly flea/tick and heartworm prevention.

animal.description:
Tuck is a 3 year old neutered male American Bulldog mix. 

**Tuck is shown by appointment only. For more information or to set up an appointment, contact Rachael at rwilson@midlandshumanesociety.org or (712)396-2265**

Tuck is a sweet, but sensitive fellow looking for a laid back home where he can acclimate at his own pace. Tuck likes to play but has moderate-low energy. He would prefer to snooze on the couch next to you instead! 

Tuck needs a home with experience with large breeds. He is very strong & might be protective of his home or owned. He will do best in a home without a lot of visitors or commotion. 

Tuck is friendly & easy going with most people, but does not like to be handled roughly so we recommend a home with adults only.
Tuck did not do well with animals in his previous home so he wants to soak up all the attention as your only pet!

Tuck is not suitable for apartment living & a fence is required. 

This is an adult dog and the adoption cost is $150, which covers microchip, all shots, and spaying or neutering. Come out to meet all of our adoptable animals today!

Are you looking to adopt? If what you're searching for is a personable, healthy, happy and playful dog... search no more! ShelleyMac is the perfect match for you!

ShelleyMac is intelligent, trusting, and loving 8-year old Labrador/Pittie mix, (8/26/12) who is SOOO full of life, love, excitement, and curiosity. You will quickly see that ShellyMac has an extremely sweet and happy disposition, and she has a constant smile on her face to prove it. Shelley would like to be an only child, no other pets, or children in the house as she wants you all to herself!

ShelleyMac has excellent house manners, is crate trained, but doesn't really need to be crated. She answers to commands like come, sit, and stay, and barks only at appropriate times (such as when someone is at the door).

ShelleyMac LOVES playing fetch, riding in the car, getting hugged, kissed and cuddled!

It's completely amazing that her big heart fits in her small body! If you decide to adopt ShelleyMac, you will consider yourself EXTREMELY lucky!! She's definitely a keeper!!

This goofball loves to play with other dogs and loves people.  Hondo has extremely short hair that unfortunately causes him to get marked up very easily when he plays with his buddies.  Hondo loves to snuggle and curl up with his humans and enjoys being close to his people.  Hondo is 70 pounds and loves playing with his toys and chase around the yard with all his doggy buddies, he would love a home with a big yard!  Hondo is an extremely strong agile boy that can jump around 3-4 ft so needs a 6 ft fence he is a good boy and stays in the yard.  Although Hondo has been great with both male and female fosters, for long term success we think a female friend is preferable.  No cats for this boy.  Hondo is fixed, microchipped,  and fully vaccinated.  

If you are interested in meeting this sweet boy, please fill out an application http://ozziespoundpuppies.org/online-application/. Adoption fee is $275
All dogs adopted are up to date on shots, dewormed, microchip and fixed. We will assist in introductions to other family members, both human and furry ones. Our adoption fee is $275.00

animal.description: Rex is a huge, sweet baby. He wants attention all the time and loves to cuddle. Hes very friendly to people who are welcomed into his space, but can be timid around men outside. Hes excited to meet people and show off his toys! He LOVES walking and gets really excited when he sees the leash. Rex was unfortunately attacked by another dog in his past and is dog selective. In the shelter he did well with other dogs in the "daycare" setting, but is now working through some leash aggression issues when he is outdoors and on walks. He does get along well with a female staffy owned by the foster's friend. Rex needs a capable owner with bully-breed experience who is willing to put time and patience into socializing him and desensitizing him to animal stimulation when walking. A home with a fenced in yard would be best, but an owner without a yard who is committed to working through his quirks with a professional trainer would also be okay. He should be the only dog in the home. He has a ton of love to give his people and would love nothing more than to snuggle up in a forever home!

animal.description: Jacey, has come a long way since she came to use from a feral community of dogs who lived along busy Moreland Avenue. Adjusting to life as a shelter dog has required a lot of courage and strength of this small shepherd-mix girl. We didn't want to push Jacey beyond her comfort zone, so we have moved slowly, and have been steadily working to gain her trust. It is working, and we think she is ready to find her home. She needs a hero. She needs someone who can see beyond her fear and really see HER. Jacey needs a quiet, stable home with or without dogs, where she can relax. She needs someone patient, who will love and protect her. She feels vulnerable outside her routine, so she can be a flight risk. She needs someone to show her the ropes and help her find her way. Jacey may never be a traditional dog-park, socially adept "pet me" kind of dog, but she will still be a wonderful companion. She needs you. Her eyes say it all. No kids, please. Questions? Message us. #adoptadog #whywerescue #thinkrescue

animal.description:
Our love affair with Milo the Love Potato goes way back. We met him years ago, when he was a young pup someone dropped over our shelter fence one night. When we first saw him, he bounded out of darkness and we froze, unsure of what to do. We still laugh about that moment six years later. All wiggly-bottomed and excited, he plopped down, rolled onto his back, legs splayed in all directions, for a belly rub. Instantly, we fell in love with his sweetness. It's hard not to. Two of our staffers fostered Milo in their home, along with two other pibble-mixes, and they were a dream team together. He was perfect. So, perfect, his foster moms knew Milo would thrive in an adoptive home. He found a family, and was adopted along with another puggle from PAWS Atlanta. They would be BFF's for 5+ years, until Milo's puggle companion and his beloved human father passed away within a short time of each other. Milo's mom eventually decided to adopt another young dog who, in turn, Milo did not take to. So, he is back with us, and back at square one again. But, here's the thing:
Milo is grown now (almost 8) and he's a tripod (accident long ago in his home), and he's a little bewildered and saddened by his change of fortune. But, he's still perfect. He's funny, endearing, playful, up-for-anything, adores car rides and feeling his ears flapping in the wind. He's still wiggly-bottomed and joyful. He's still a lapdog, through and through. 
He's impossible to photograph because he immediately drops on his back as splays himself out like a russet potato at your feet. He's just a good, good, good boy. 
We think he would feel most comfortable as an only dog. We're not sure on cats, but we can test him. Milo is such a great dog. If you're interested in meeting him, please fill out an adoption application at PAWSAtlanta.org and we'll get you scheduled for an appointment to come spend some time with Milo.

animal.description:
***COVID 19 NOVEMBER 2020 PROTOCOL***

Due to the surge of Covid 19 and statewide restrictions, we are adopting to LOCAL (CLALLAM AND JEFFERSON COUNTY) RESIDENTS ONLY. We are not doing adoptions to Canada at this time due to the border closure. We do not ship animals. 

All potential adopters must fill out an adoption application prior to setting up an appointment to meet the animal. An application can be found on our website.

We have limited staff during this time, please allow 3-5 business days for us to process your application. We are screening the applications for the first BEST fit for each animal. 

If you are approved, you will be contacted by us via phone or email.

NAME: Hawk
AGE: About 2 years
WEIGHT: About 50 lbs
BREED(S): Pit bull mix
REASON FOR ARRIVAL: Transfer from California

GENERAL INFO ABOUT PERSONALITY: Hawk is a goofy young boy with lots of learning to do. He is very intelligent and is picking up clicker training and many commands quickly! He absolutely loves his toys and playing around outside and is very food motivated.

When Hawk sees other dogs on leash or through a fence, he will get overstimulated and bark. He definitely needs work on learning to be calm when he sees other animals, which is something we are working on with him. At this time he should not live with other dogs and he most likely will not be good with cats.

Hawk will need a calm owner who will establish clear boundaries and be the leader. He does really well with a calm handler who does not let him get away with things such as jumping up or chewing on the leash. He will need someone who will direct him on how to behave but encourage him to do so in a positive way (he has been making great progress with clicker and treat training!). 

Hawk is a very intelligent dog and a playful guy but is not for a first time dog owner nor an apartment. He really is just an overgrown puppy who is still learning how to be a good boy. 

Hawk has had many hours of training at OPHS, and his adoption fee will include an hour of training for his adopter from our KPA certified trainer. 

Activity Level? High
Training Needs? High
House Trained? Unknown
Leash Trained? Yes 
Comfortable with kids? Recommend no kids because he's easily over stimulated
Comfortable with strangers? Might need a little time to warm up
History with other dogs? Unknown, at this time we are saying no dogs
History with cats? Unknown but most likely not good

Additional MEDICAL notes: None

animal.description:
Sandy wandered into her rescuer's yard and announced she was looking for a loving, responsible family.  

With a guesstimated birthday in May 2012, Sandy weighs about 45 lb.  She loves to talk and will chat as long as it takes to get her point across.  She will also bark obnoxiously if left outside unattended.

Sandy is very affectionate and loves people.  She likes car rides and other polite dogs.

Whether dogs / puppies come in as strays or owner surrenders, we usually have to make our best guess as to birthdate and breed.   

If adopted into a home with other animals, particularly cats, your new pet should be crated or secured when you're not available to supervise to insure a harmonious relationship.  

A vet reference is required to confirm responsible pet ownership.  We suggest first time pet owners look for an adult dog for companionship and to gain experience.

Adoption fee covers two vaccinations plus spay / neuter if using our local low-cost spay/neuter clinic (overnight stay required) and surgery occurs as agreed upon in the adoption contract.  Convenience fee equal to refundable spay/neuter deposit may be added if using our veterinarian.  Additional fees for 3rd puppy vaccination, refundable spay/neuter deposit, etc. may apply.  

We are an all-volunteer, foster-based rescue.  We receive no funding from agencies.  Available animals can be seen most Saturdays at Tractor Supply in Lenoir from 10:00 a.m. to 2:00 p.m.  We recommend interested parties contact us to pre-qualify for adoption so their new furry family can go home once paperwork is complete.  Fees are required in cash.  For more information on our organization, our website is www.petpartnersrescue.org.

animal.description:
Looking for an energetic 68 pound gal who will alert you to anything that seems amiss inside or outside? Give you a diving hello? Think racing around is really fun - both inside and out? And most importantly, love you with her whole heart and then some? Then Delfina is the "Girl" for you! (We nicknamed her Girl!) Delfina is all this and more. She's over the top, living life full blast. And she just knows there's a someone out there who will be as devoted to her as she will be to them. 

Just look at her sweet face! She is a happy and fun-loving dog who loves, Loves, LOVES her people! Delfina will benefit from ongoing training to channel her enthusiasm and help her learn boundaries and appropriate play spaces. (She's already nailed the crate training and is housebroken - yay Delfina!) Delfina probably isn't best in a house with wee ones (see the part about diving hellos). She will thrive in a home where she has outdoor space to run around and/or with a family that goes on long walks, or jogs or hikes - you get the idea, this gal needs exercise and space to minimize indoor "zoomies." You can turn everything into a game, as she sniffs out her food, and works for treats. Developing a routine that includes mentally and physically stimulating activities will created a tuckered out pup who will welcome an end of the day snuggle. Delfina isn't sure about other pets and new people as much as she is her "family people," but give her some time and go slow for increased chances of success in her spreading her love around. https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=_JvHR6L_pQc&showinfo=0

If you think you're the person, or family, to fulfill Delfina's needs, and in return be rewarded with a fantastic, loving companion, send an email to blanchard.michaela@gmail.com and let us know how Delfina would be a great fit in your life.

animal.description:
Meet Nellie!

Nellie is a 9 year old female pitbull mix! Nellie was brought into the Mutt Misfits program through a seizure of a local fighting and baiting ring. Nellie was one of many dogs taken from the ring to rehabilitate and help them find their furever homes! Nellie is spayed, up to date on all age appropriate vaccinations, preventatives and she's micro-chipped.

***This dog, along with the over 20 other dogs rescued from a fighting ring, has been assessed for behavior and temperament and approved for adoption. However, since we had training sessions donated to us, we are erring on the side of caution and slowly sending them all through behavioral training that will teach them basic manners and give them a good structure to build on with their forever family. Please inquire as to the status of this dog's training if you're interested in meeting and possibly adopting! The most important thing to us is to ensure that these dogs' horrendous past does not affect the future they deserve to have! ***

Nellie is crate trained and potty trained. She has accidents due to being an older lady, but will do it on a designated potty pad! Nellie walks politely on a leash and doesn't care about other dogs on her walks! She rides well in the car and loves to go on special outings for Puppucinos and chicken nuggets. Nellie knows basic commands such as sit, come when called, etc.

Nellie has been through an absurd amount of abuse in her life time and it shows in her lack of socialization. Nellie has very awkward social skills and is actively working on making friends with her foster siblings, but much prefers to be with her foster parents and other people! The behavior based training program will help develop her social skills, but Nellie would thrive in a house hold without other animals. She has not been around children or cats. 

At first when Nellie went into her foster home, she had to be picked up and carried out of the car due to being so scared. She was silent and cowered in the corner of her bed in her room. Her foster mom sat in her room and worked on the floor for days to gain her trust. It took her weeks to let her foster dad come near her or even touch her. She didn't understand toys or snacks, but slowly and surely she got more comfortable with her foster parents. She now jumps up on her foster dad and their guests when she plays and doesn't have any fears! She actually prefers her foster dad now, because he plays her favorite game "Catch the Piggy" where they chase each other in the yard like a game of tag. Nellie will crawl onto anyone's lap (despite being a chunky girl at 70lbs) and take a happy nap! Nellie is a sweet old lady with a big personality. She has very few teeth due to them being ground down and removed from her abusers. Nellie almost understands how to play fetch and loves to chase after anything you'll throw for her - she hasn't mastered bringing anything back but it's still a very fun game for her. Nellie likes to make nests in all blankets she finds and curls up on the couch to binge watch Netflix! Despite the abuse she's suffered, Nellie has persevered and now loves to be a normal dog. She took a few weeks to get used to men and any new visitors, but has now warmed up to everyone she meets and has always been very loving. Nellie has an infectious-toothless smile and you can't help but fall in love with her!


You can apply to meet / adopt her at www.muttmisfits.com/adoption-application
