Chihuahua
Male, 11 years old, 9 pounds
Godric, named after a very noble Harry Potter character who was one of the founders of Hogwarts, is available for adoption, and he is so sweet. 

If you are looking for a mellow companion for short walks, lots of snuggling, and is a good listener, then please consider Godric. He is good with other dogs and has enjoyed the contact and attention he has received from new people. 

Godric is doing really well after an initial scare. There was fear he would need to be put to sleep because he was acting very odd, and we were contacted to see if our veterinarian could help. He seemed dazed, confused and unable to walk. We hustled out there as soon as we could, determined to help. We had our medical director come to check him out. Our vet believes he had a negative reaction to something. We are happy to report that he is now up and walking and even eating and drinking. We are SO glad that we can offer him a second chance. Despite being a senior, he certainly still has a lot of life left to live. 

He came to us from Monterey County Animal Services.

animal.description:
Meet Duke. He's a very special boy. We got a call on 1/31/19 that a lady was moving and she couldn't take her dog so we helped her out. She asked if she could visit a week later and let us know that prior to surrendering him, he had gotten out and bit a kid on the way to school. It did not break the skin but he was deemed dangerous until court. The hearing was held the end of March and poor Duke was deemed dangerous so when he's adopted and we have faith there is a perfect home for him, they will have to abide by the dangerous dog rules for their county. The county wanted Animal Friends to surrender Duke but we would not so they worked with us explaining the laws and paperwork that needed filed. He is now the owners of the rescue and being cross-posted until we can find a home for him. He's a sweet boy once he knows you and is very food motivated. He's house trained and has NEVER had an accident since we've had him. He will greet you each time holding his bowl and he loves toys. We have not had any incidents other than him jumping up on us to go for car rides. He's very strong and needs obedience training, like any 2 year old shepherd/pit mix. He does well with other dogs once he knows them and lived with a child that was about 9 years old. We were told that he loves to snuggle and slept in bed with his previous family.

Because Duke is deemed dangerous, we will arrange meet and greets cautiously and do introductions slowly. He will not be at the adoption events because we don't want to risk another bite. His eyes and personality melted our hearts and we are so thankful Prince William County worked with us to keep this guy alive.

If interested, applications can be completed at animalfriendsva.org then go to animals and scroll down to Duke. He will need registered as a dangerous dog where ever he is adopted which is $150. Therefore, his adoption fee is $150 which is half price. $150 to Animal Friends and $150 for the dangerous dog fee. If you have questions about the laws in Prince William, please feel free to email us at va.animalfriends@gmail.com.

We look forward to hearing from you.

animal.description: Charlie is a cute little guy who needs a quiet environment and people who are willing to give him time and their understanding and patience. He gets overwhelmed easily and shows it by growling at people. He needs people who understand that his aggressive behavior is the result of fear and not anything personal. For example, he joyfully wags his tail when his foster family comes home and has tolerated a few seconds of petting, but then he goes back to keeping his distance. He will also occasionally sit in his foster Mom's lap and press his head against her arm (she hasn't tried to pet him in those moments because she doesn't want to ruin them by triggering his anxiety). He loves going for walks, but hates moving vehicles (maybe he was hit by a car at some point in his life?), and has shown that he will play bow (only after getting to know his foster for several weeks). We do not recommend him for families with small children.

animal.description: Hi! My name is Kinzey, and I am a 6 year old American Foxhound mix. I was adopted 4 years ago, and my new mommy and I were absolutely crazy about each other. Sadly, my new mommy passed away suddenly and unexpectedly. Now, I am back in a foster home, and while I really like it here, I would love to find my fur-ever home again. I am a silly, smart, loveable, playful cuddlebug. I like to play, but I am perfectly content to amuse myself while you do your thing, and I love to snuggle up next to you while you relax. I give the best hugs!!! I'm a little shy around new people, but with a little time and patience, I always come around. I am house-trained and love to go for car rides and WALKS - walks are the BEST!!! My foster says that I am close to being the PERFECT DOG. I attach to my family very quickly and have some anxiety when they leave me alone. I can bust out of crates and would do best in a home with a stay at home parent, not a necessity; however, I have destroyed some things I shouldn't have, such as carpeting and walls because I was trying to get to my family. I am spayed, microchipped, and up to date on all my vaccinations. If you would like to meet me (and I sure HOPE you do!), I will be at our adoption events. We're at the Potomac Mills PetSmart every Sunday from 12:30 - 3:00. The address is 13337 Worth Ave, Woodbridge VA 22192. On the 2nd Saturday of each month we are also at the Lorton PetValu located at 9427 Lorton Market St, Lorton VA. We're there from 12:00 - 2:00. You can also fill out a no-obligation, online application at animalfriendsva.org/animals, and scroll down to Kinzey, (the pretty one waiting for a home!). On that page is my application.

animal.description:
Hi! I'm Nusta. I am an energetic 1.5-year-old female Jack Russell/Pitbull Mix. I was adopted 5 months ago into a home with a 2-year-old male dog, and due to the COVID restrictions shortly after my adoption, I was not able to get the right socializing and professional training I needed to make sure I had a great start to my new life. Now that I've had time to decompress after shelter life, and with guidance from my Vet, I've decided I want to be the only fur baby in my owner's heart, and need to find a new forever home that can provide me with that. I love walks and all physical activity, my nickname is Shakira because I can't stop shaking my hips when I see a leash. I make a great running and hiking buddy, and sticking my head out a car window is my favorite thing. I need a home with no other animals and no small children as I get very protective over my stuffed toys. I also require an experienced owner who will give me the structure and daily exercise I need to be a happy girl. I am housebroken, crate trained for overnight sleep, and very well-behaved indoors and respectful of furniture. I like to please and give my humans love every chance I get, and I can also entertain myself when needed. My current family has acquired a lot of great supplies for me that I will take to my new home, including XL Crate with memory foam mattress, training collar with remote, hands-free leash, rain, and snow coats. I'm also on a great Banfield wellness plan that can be transferred over to cover my remaining puppy shots and tests until December 2020. My current family knows that I will need professional training and willing to provide a stipend to the new owner to make sure I make it my forever home and get the life I deserve. I look forward to making you smile every day with my adorable Jack Russell ears and soulful honey-colored eyes.

Please contact Rose at vineyardsocials@gmail.com

animal.description:
Hi meet Ava,

Ava is a lovely 1-2 year old, Pit mix. She is deaf but is working on learning some commands, she is a smart and happy girl. Ava loves playing with other dogs and toys but is also an amazing snuggler. She is a happy go lucky girl and she makes a great companion. Ava is looking for a home that has patience and someone that is willing to learn with her or someone that has worked with deaf dogs before. She also needs a home where she is going to be the only dog.She wants a home that is committed to taking her to obedience classes while continuing her socialization. She is young, so she needs a plan if there are longer workdays, so she is not spending too much time in a crate.

Ava came to us after our rescue staff saw her on media platforms. She stole our heart and so we brought her to our rescue where we can find her the perfect family

We hold an event every weekend at our facility on SATURDAY 11-5pm.   Please visit our social media platforms for the specifics for each weekend as it changes from week to week. Please find our application at lovejoyfoundation.org when you come to an event please bring that filled out in hand with you. You can find our application at Lovejoyfoundation.orgYou MUST submit an APPLICATION via email in hopes to get an appointment, our application is found on our website lovejoyfoundation.org. If you do not get a phone call by Friday then we did not have anything available for you or the pet of interest was adopted before we got you application. We are a Southern California based rescue and do nothing adopt further than an hour from our headquarters in Inglewood, Ca. we do not adopt out more than a 30 minute radius. We appreciate you being understanding and Patient as we attempt to go back to a new normal.

animal.description:
Are you looking for a running partner? If yes, I might just be the perfect partner for you! My name is Zelma and I absolutely LOVE going for runs or nice long walks. I have this thing called a virtual foster mom and she likes to come to get me on Sunday mornings and take me for long runs because I tend to have a lot of energy. So someone that can help me get that energy out and that has a fenced-in yard would be amazing for me! 

Now let me tell you a little bit about my skills because they are amazing! I went to this place they call board and train and got to spend 30 days with them. This doesn't make me a bad dog, in fact, it makes me an amazing dog. I'm great on a leash (which makes my walks/runs super easy) and I will heel by your left side as long as you give me the command. I also know how to sit, down, stay, bed, short recall commands, leave it (great for those rabbits we see on our runs/walls) among other great skills like loving my people! 

So let me tell you when I find people that I love they are my people. I just want to please them and make them happy. I need my person/persons to be strong leaders for me. I want to please them, but I need them to be my boss and set the boundaries with me. Once I know you mean business we will be good to go. So while I love humans I don't really love the 4 legged companions as much. I've learned skills at board and train that have helped me with that, but I do need to be the only dog in the home. I can be picky about the dogs that I choose to allow in my space. This is where needing a strong leader to just tell me to leave it when we meet other dogs and whatnot will come into play. My foster mom or the great team at the rescue are more than happy to speak to you more about this and answer any questions you may have about my temperament. 

You see I'm lucky enough to be in this unique situation that the rescue has agreed to allow me to do something that is outside of their normal process called "Foster to Adopt". That is how much they believe in me and know how good I can do in the right home! I know, AMAZING right! 

Do you want to be my running or walking buddy? If yes please fill out an application for me today and maybe we can meet! 

* This dog is approved to live in Denver, however; BSL restrictions may apply in other cities/counties as applicable. Homeownership is required!

Estimated DOB: 5/19/17

Adoption fee includes the following:


	Spay/Neuter
	Rabies Vaccination
	Distemper / Parvo Vaccines (includes series of 3 for puppies)
	Bordetella
	Microchip with prepaid lifetime registration
	Deworming

animal.description:
Loki was picked up as a stray and has been with our rescue for over 7 months. He was surrendered to the SPCA of East Texas since his finders were unable to keep him. He is a German Shepherd mix with an estimated birth date of 5/29/19. This breed is known to be very active, loyal, and yes even stubborn! Loki is a high energy dog and will require a home with a 6 ft. privacy fence. He can scale anything shorter. Loki is smart boy and knows a few basic commands. He is extremely loyal and has been failed by humans several times now that he does have some separation anxiety. With someone who is patient, Loki would make a great companion doggy. He would love to be the only dog in his home but will do well with others if properly introduced. He cannot be in a home with cats. He loves toys especially rope and squeaky toys. Loki is housebroken and knows how to use a dog door if needed. He will require an owner who is active and can give Loki daily exercise!

To adopt Loki, please complete an online adoption application at www.spcaeasttx.com under the "adopt a dog" tab!
